<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> take the wind • take wind</xh5><p> <i>take the wind</i>—(sl.) take one’s leave; make a hasty retreat <i>(also: take the breeze): </i>I <u>took the wind</u> just as soon as I could get over the wall and get out of here.</p><p> <i>take wind</i>—(of a rumor, etc.) become known <i>(also: take air):</i> The preparations for Margaret’s flight had not been conducted so secretly but that some rumor of them had <u>taken wind</u>.</p> </entry>
